# How to Use Claude Code with Qwen Models â€” 100% Free

This guide explains how to run Claude Code (ccr) using Qwen models locally for free.

Requirements:
- Qwen CLI (installed & authenticated)
- Node.js v18+

------------------------------------------------------------
1. Install Qwen Code CLI
------------------------------------------------------------

Run:

npm install -g @qwen-code/qwen-code@latest

Verify:

qwen --version

------------------------------------------------------------
2. Find Your Qwen Access Token
------------------------------------------------------------

After running "qwen", your token is stored here:

C:\Users\PC_USER\.qwen\oauth_creds.json

Example:

{
  "access_token": "YOUR_QWEN_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE",
  "token_type": "Bearer",
  "refresh_token": "YOUR_QWEN_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE",
  "resource_url": "portal.qwen.ai",
  "expiry_date": 1764876220290
}

Copy the "access_token" and use it in config.

------------------------------------------------------------
3. Update Claude Code Router Config
------------------------------------------------------------

Paste this full config:

{
  "LOG": true,
  "LOG_LEVEL": "info",
  "HOST": "127.0.0.1",
  "PORT": 3456,
  "API_TIMEOUT_MS": 600000,
  "Providers": [
    {
      "name": "qwen",
      "api_base_url": "https://portal.qwen.ai/v1/chat/completions",
      "api_key": "YOUR_QWEN_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE",
      "models": [
        "qwen3-coder-plus",
        "qwen3-coder-plus",
        "qwen3-coder-plus"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "Router": {
    "default": "qwen,qwen3-coder-plus",
    "background": "qwen,qwen3-coder-plus",
    "think": "qwen,qwen3-coder-plus",
    "longContext": "qwen,qwen3-coder-plus",
    "longContextThreshold": 60000,
    "webSearch": "qwen,qwen3-coder-plus"
  }
}

Replace api_key with your real token.

------------------------------------------------------------
4. Start Using Claude Code with Qwen
------------------------------------------------------------

Restart router:

ccr restart

Start Claude Code:

ccr code

Test:

> hi

------------------------------------------------------------
5. Fixing 401 Unauthorized Token Errors
------------------------------------------------------------

If token expires:

1. Delete file:
   C:\Users\PC_USER\.qwen\oauth_creds.json

2. Re-login:
   qwen

3. Copy new access_token and paste into config
   "api_key": "YOUR_QWEN_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE"

